divs: Sighting Details I went outside that evening to get pictures of stars, planets. maybe a galaxy, by holding my digital camera to the lens of the telescope. I went into my backyard, Into a dark spot, away from all lights. I wanted to get pictures of stars! I would point the telescope at an object, hold the camera up to the lens and shoot. There was no un-natural movement, Not even a plane went overhead that night. After about 20 pictures, I came into the house to download the photos. When I ran a slideshow, there were only two photos that were not black or blured. I went to the first one, It looked like a planet with and explosion off of the side... That left me scratching my head, I do not know what that was! The second picture , when I zoomed in on it, it took my breath away! I am sure that it is not nature made... It is not shaped like the ISS. I do not think that it looks like a sattelite. None that I have ever seen! I have sent the pictures to a few people that I believed would give be an idea of what I have, No Response! I guess that I should have not expected one from NASA, Space weather! Could you please take a look and give me your opinion? Thank You, Patty Smith
Summary: I was just taking pictures of stars
